INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'ce2794c2-47db-46d5-a153-7e0eb90c8b33',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Ansible Idempotency — Write Playbooks That Are Safe to Run Twice$escape$,
  $escape$Ansible pushes configuration over SSH without agents on target hosts — the control node connects, executes modules, and disconnects. The contract is idempotency: running a playbook ten times must produce identical state to running it once. Most built-in modules honor this automatically. `ansible.builtin.package` checks installed state before touching the package manager. `ansible.builtin.copy` hashes file content and skips the transfer if unchanged. `ansible.builtin.user` reads `/etc/passwd` before creating accounts. Where idempotency breaks down is `ansible.builtin.command` and `ansible.builtin.shell` — these run unconditionally unless guarded with `creates`, `removes`, or a `when` conditional tied to a registered variable. Prefer purpose-built modules over shell commands wherever possible; they carry the idempotency guarantee built in. For truly stateful operations (database migrations, one-time bootstraps), use `run_once: true` combined with a sentinel file checked via `ansible.builtin.stat` to prevent re-execution. Structure playbooks as declarations of desired state, not imperative scripts, and Ansible's check mode (`--check`) becomes a free dry-run across your entire fleet.$escape$,
  $escape$- name: Ensure nginx config is deployed
  hosts: webservers
  become: true
  tasks:
    - name: Install nginx
      ansible.builtin.package:
        name: nginx
        state: present

    - name: Deploy config template
      ansible.builtin.template:
        src: nginx.conf.j2
        dest: /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
        owner: root
        mode: '0644'
      notify: Reload nginx

    - name: Run migration only once
      ansible.builtin.command: /opt/app/migrate.sh
      args:
        creates: /opt/app/.migrated

  handlers:
    - name: Reload nginx
      ansible.builtin.service:
        name: nginx
        state: reloaded$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
